According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by Ukrainian special services.
The US authorities forced Mask to leave the post of Chairman of the Board of Tesla
American businessman Elon Musk will leave the post of chairman of the board of directors of the Tesla company founded by him at the request of the US authorities.
To settle the claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $ 20 million.
According to CNBC, a pre-trial agreement with the agency allows Musk to remain in a senior position at Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $ 20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed in his place.
It is specified that the agreement still needs to be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the US Securities and Exchange Commission accused Mask of misleading shareholders with a statement about the availability of sufficient funds to buy back the shares of this company and filed a lawsuit against the entrepreneur.
We are talking about the publication of the businessman in Twitter, where he announced his desire to buy back Tesla shares at $420 apiece, but never did it.
After the tweet, the company's shares rose by almost 11%.
The head of the British foreign Ministry compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Secretary Jeremy Hunt compared the EU to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of enslaving member states.
The diplomat made this statement at the congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
As noted by the Daily Mail, thus Hunt commented on the difficulties in the negotiation process on Brexit.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave it.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from a community into a prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who will want to escape from captivity,” the minister said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only aggravate the crisis, Gazeta.ru notes.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that Brexit negotiations had come to a standstill.
She commented on the results of the informal summit of the European Union in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 following a referendum.
It is expected that the withdrawal of the United Kingdom will take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
The issue of the Irish border remains open.
