Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal bailiff service of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and ensuring information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself, more than 42 thousand visits to the section "Bank of data of enforcement proceedings", 661 payment receipts for payment of debts were downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council of the Federal Security Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan, almost every resident of the region has debts for utility payments, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is immune from unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the FSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends everyone who has planned a trip abroad to clarify in the bailiffs’ department at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service has created a "Data Bank of enforcement proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional sites of the FSBSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communications iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk bailiffs in respect of all debtors, - explains Delgir Bodgaeva, assistant head of the FSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
In the presence of debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the writ of execution or other act; its numbers, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiffs’ department; the name of the bailiff-executor; contact phone number.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
